OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1779307555
OL,3,CLabour could beat Reform in general
OL,4,Celection if led by Andy Burnham, polls
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FFour in 10 of those surveyed from
OL,8,Facross the political spectrum believed
OL,9,FMr Burnham had done a good job as
OL,10,FGreater Manchester mayor, compared to
OL,11,Fless than 1 in 10 saying he had done a
OL,12,Fbad job.
OL,14,FBut answers were less clear-cut when
OL,15,Fasked whether he would be a good prime
OL,16,Fminister, with 31% thinking he would,
OL,17,F20% saying he would not, and nearly
OL,18,Fhalf giving no opinion.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
